    • linear_regression.Update

    Author:

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      (package private) double alpha
      alpha is the step size of iterations
      (package private) java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Double> costHistory
      costHistory contains the costFunction history as a function of iteration#, if the fit is going well the cost should decrease with every iteration, if the cost is increasing the fit may begin to diverge
      (package private) int iterations
      number of updates to theta
      (package private) double m
      m is the number of training examples = y.length and x.length
      (package private) double[] theta
      theta is the array of the fitting paramaters
      (package private) double[][] x
      each row of x corresponds to 1 training example, so you can have any number of parameters that you want
      (package private) double[][] x_bias
      x_bias is the same as the x matrix but with a column of 1's prepended to x, so that we can have an intercept term in our fit
      (package private) double[] y
      each element of y corresponds to 1 training example
